Third-party models
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The build and runtime fetch machine-learning models from third parties. These
models are NOT vendored in this repository; they are downloaded by your own
build/runtime from their upstream sources, and their own licenses govern their
use and any redistribution.

1. Static text-embedding model (crate: ese)
   Source: sentence-transformers/static-retrieval-mrl-en-v1
           https://huggingface.co/sentence-transformers/static-retrieval-mrl-en-v1
   License: Apache-2.0
   Use here: ese/build.rs downloads the model weights and tokenizer at build
   time and bakes a quantized/truncated copy of the weights into the compiled
   crate. Redistribution of a build artifact therefore redistributes derived
   weights under the upstream Apache-2.0 license.

2. Document-layout detection model (crate: library-ingest)
   Source: Oblix/yolov10m-doclaynet_ONNX_document-layout-analysis
           https://huggingface.co/Oblix/yolov10m-doclaynet_ONNX_document-layout-analysis
   License: AGPL-3.0
   Use here: fetched at runtime to data/models/layout/ and run via ONNX Runtime
   for page-layout detection during ingestion. It is optional in the sense that
   ingestion falls back to a word-gap heuristic when the model file is absent.
   Because this model is AGPL-3.0, review its terms before redistributing it or
   offering it as part of a network service.
